The paper discusses the use of generative adversarial networks for probabilistic forecasting, which is a topic that falls under the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE), signal processing (cs.SI), and information theory (cs.IT). Given the focus on machine learning and neural networks, cs.LG and cs.NE are the most likely sub-categories. However, the paper also discusses the use of probabilistic methods and information theory, which makes cs.AI, cs.SI, and cs.IT also likely sub-categories.
